snippet.textDisplay: Jacob Eason was a tremendous QB in high school.  The sideline routes though he appears to be throwing just a hair late, driving the receiver out of bounds.  I do think that college coaches maybe forced him to change his mechanics perhaps.  I watched his high school highlights and said, “Wow!”  He had a really quick release and could probably throw off-platform and off his back foot better than any high school guy I’ve ever seen.  But now his throwing motion is more classic and I’d personally like to see him throw like he used to again.  But the whole Georgia thing must’ve been a bad experience for him because I believe he lost his starting role to Fromm after an injury, and never got it back.  Then Jacob transferred to the UW — my alma mater — sat for a year maybe, and played pretty well as a Husky.  I heard that the Patriots and maybe Titans are thinking about drafting him.  I think all this stuff is right but I’ve been wrong before.
snippet.textOriginal: Jacob Eason was a tremendous QB in high school.  The sideline routes though he appears to be throwing just a hair late, driving the receiver out of bounds.  I do think that college coaches maybe forced him to change his mechanics perhaps.  I watched his high school highlights and said, “Wow!”  He had a really quick release and could probably throw off-platform and off his back foot better than any high school guy I’ve ever seen.  But now his throwing motion is more classic and I’d personally like to see him throw like he used to again.  But the whole Georgia thing must’ve been a bad experience for him because I believe he lost his starting role to Fromm after an injury, and never got it back.  Then Jacob transferred to the UW — my alma mater — sat for a year maybe, and played pretty well as a Husky.  I heard that the Patriots and maybe Titans are thinking about drafting him.  I think all this stuff is right but I’ve been wrong before.

snippet.textDisplay: When Love throws, especially on those outs, I think it takes too long for the ball to hit the target.  I think Trent Dilfer has a name for the amount of time when a QB starts his throwing motion until when the ball his the receiver’s hands, something like “Load-to-target.”  That’s probably the wrong name but it’s the general idea.  But it looks like Love’s number might be poor on a standard out.
